THE Kogi State government through the Land and Housing Services Bureau has acquired automated Certificate of Occupancy Machine in order to curtail the incidence of racketeering and unlawful grabbing of land, delay in the issuance of the certificate of occupancy. During the unveiling of the machine in the Governor’s office on Friday, Governor Yahaya Bello commended the Bureau for ensuring that his administration’s policy in the area of land reform was yielding result. Earlier, the Director-General, Land and Housing Services Bureau, Hajia Mariam Ladi Ibrahim commended Governor Yahaya Bello for the genuine reform the Bureau has witnessed under his leadership. Ghana president, first lady thrilled at FOCOS charity for… Facebook removes coordinated fake accounts in Nigeria, UAE,… Facebook launches Threads from Instagram, new camera-first… Nigeria Customs Service explains reason for operation at… ALSO READ: https://tribuneonlineng.com/much-ado-about-vat-and-charges/ Hajia Mariam noted that under the last administrations, about a thousand certificates were properly issued to landowners stressing that the current administration has signed five hundred certificates while an additional six hundred were ready for signing. Aside fast-tracking the process of Certificate issuance, she noted with the Automated machine, issues of fake C of O, land racketeering would be things of the past. How premature ejaculation  and small penis almost ruin my marriage and made my wife cheat on me, until my Abuja doctor recommend this powerful but simple solution that work wonder...DONT BE A VICTIM.... SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
